    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN314-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. aiyūrmuṭavaṉār
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN314">
<l>maṉaikkuviḷak kākiya vāṇutal kaṇavaṉ</l>
<l>muṉaikkuvaram pākiya veṉvē ṉeṭuntakai</l>
<l>naṭukaṟ piṟaṅkiya vuvaliṭu paṟantalaip</l>
<l>puṉkāḻ nelli vaṉpulac cīṟūrk</l>
<l>kuṭiyu maṉṉun tāṉē koṭiyeṭuttu</l>
<l>niṟaiyaḻin teḻutaru tāṉaikkuc</l>
<l>ciṟaiyun tāṉētaṉ ṉiṟaiviḻu muṟiṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The husband of [her with] bright forehead who has become the light of the house,</l>
<l>the paragon with a victoriuous spear who has become the border of the frontier,</l>
<l>for the little village with hard soil [and] myrobalan tress with puny cores,</l>
<l>in the waste lands where foliage has been placed that glistens with hero stones,</l>
<l>he is the family and the lord, and he is also the dam</l>
<l>for the army that rises, shrunk in size, raising banners,</l>
<l>when his lord prevails/is in trouble.  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
